-- Thailand Stocks: Airports of Thailand, Asia Aviation, Thai Air
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-07-13T09:49:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/thailand-stocks-airports-of-thailand-sriracha-construction.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 1.4 percent to 1,210.29, the highest
close since May 8. The gauge gained 0.9 percent this week, a
third weekly advance.  Tourism-related companies:  Airports of Thailand Pcl  (AOT
TB), the nation’s largest airport operator, climbed 3.1 percent
to 66.50, the highest close since November 2006.  Asia Aviation
Pcl (AAV)  , the parent of the nation’s largest budget carrier,
gained 2.3 percent to 3.64 baht.  Thai Airways International Pcl (THAI) 
, the nation’s biggest carrier, increased 1.5 percent
to 20.90 baht, the most since June 15.  The number of passengers at Suvarnabhumi international
airport in June jumped 15 percent from a year earlier to 4.03
million, according to data on Airports of Thailand’s website.  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s largest oil company, gained
1.5 percent to 334 baht, the highest close since July 6. Crude
oil added as much as 60 cents to $86.68 a barrel on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange .  Sriracha Construction Pcl (SRICHA)   rose 2.7 percent to
19.40 baht, the largest increase since July 5. The company won a
202.5 million baht ($6.4 million) contract for the fabrication
of steel structures, it said in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
